The Micex Stock Exchange, Russiaâ€™s
largest bourse by volume, offered to buy Moscow rival RTS,
Kommersant reported, citing unidentified RTS shareholders
approached by Micex.  Micex offered to buy 20 percent of RTS for $150 million and
the remaining 80 percent via a share swap, the Moscow-based
newspaper reported today. The offer was made the same day RTS
declared its intention to hold an initial public offering,
